{#
  adopter-welcome.step-4.mjml — Week 4: your next best step.
  Source: Drip Emails for adopter Sign-up.docx (Email 5).
#}
{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}
{% block body %}
  <h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#2C474B;font-size:18px">Your Next Best Step</h2>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Can you believe that a month has passed since you committed to FPG
    adoption? During this month you may be asking yourself, "What can I do
    to reach them from here?" Let us explore that together today. Your next
    step may be to "take action."
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Taking action could involve you financially supporting another
    organization that will begin engaging the Frontier People Group. It
    could also involve sending workers or engaging regularly through digital
    means. Whatever your level of involvement, taking action should catalyze
    evangelistic engagement among the FPG, leading to discipleship and
    planting churches.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 12px;color:#374151">Here are a few ways to go further:</p>

  <ol style="margin:0 0 16px;padding-left:20px;color:#374151">
    <li style="margin-bottom:10px"><strong>MOBILIZE PEOPLE.</strong> Advocate for your FPG(s) to catalyze more short-term and long-term workers, prayer warriors, or vocational access platforms for Christian workers.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:10px"><strong>INVEST IN THE WORK.</strong> There are many aspects of reaching FPGs that could use support.
      <ul style="margin:6px 0 0;padding-left:20px">
        <li style="margin-bottom:4px"><em>Financial:</em> Fund evangelists, church planters, Bible translation, digital resource development, leadership development, or access initiatives such as Business as Mission.</li>
        <li><em>Skills:</em> You or the people in your sphere of influence may have much-needed language, vocational, and practical skills.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:10px"><strong>ENGAGE DIRECTLY AMONG THE FPG.</strong> Access to FPGs is found through strategic connection and engagement. This can mean being involved with direct ministry where the FPG is in their homeland. It may also include reaching them in cities they have migrated to outside their country. Engagement may even be done through social media and business. No matter the access point, connections and increased understanding will be key.</li>
    <li><strong>Be sure to watch for a "You've been matched!" email from Joshua Project.</strong> For those who agreed to collaborate with others in FPG adoption, we will reach out to you when we have an organization who facilitates partnerships to reach a certain FPG. In cases where there is no current work to reach the FPG, you may be matched with others adopting the same FPG.</li>
  </ol>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    These relationships are great places to look for opportunities to give
    of your skills and resources. In places where there is no current work,
    perhaps adopters can join together to create a network who can reach the
    FPG. The ways the Lord will use you are limitless.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 8px;color:#374151">With deep gratitude,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>
  <p style="margin:0;color:#6b7280;font-style:italic;font-size:13px">
    "For just as each of us has one body with many members, and these members
    do not all have the same function, so in Christ we, though many, form one
    body, and each member belongs to all the others." (Romans 12:4-5 NIV)
  </p>
{% endblock %}
